{"id":1044,"date":"2022-02-05T15:38:00","date_gmt":"2022-02-05T15:38:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1044"},"modified":"2022-02-06T17:08:44","modified_gmt":"2022-02-06T17:08:44","slug":"add-new-partitions-and-logical-volumes-and-swap-to-a-system-non-destructively","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1044","title":{"rendered":"Add new partitions and logical volumes, and swap to a system non-destructively"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>This guide is going to be pretty much the same as the <a href=\"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=961\">previous one<\/a> on creating partition and logical volumes. The whole purpose of this is to get general knowledge of existing file systems and free space and use this information for allocating new partitions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>First let&#8217;s check how is our file system looking now exactly<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"263\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-14.png?resize=640%2C263&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1046\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-14.png?w=688&amp;ssl=1 688w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-14.png?resize=300%2C123&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-14.png?resize=24%2C10&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-14.png?resize=36%2C15&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-14.png?resize=48%2C20&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, there is still some space on disk <strong>sdc <\/strong>and whole new disk <strong>sdd<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"ading-new-partition\">Ading new partition<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"using-fdisk\">Using fdisk <\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>fdisk \/dev\/sdc<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press n for new partition<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press f for primary<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press enter for default partition number<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press enter for default sector range<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press enter to use all the space from disk<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can type t for type and choose: Linux 83 (which is default) or LVM 8e<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press w to write <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"217\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-15.png?resize=640%2C217&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1047\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-15.png?w=724&amp;ssl=1 724w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-15.png?resize=300%2C102&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-15.png?resize=24%2C8&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-15.png?resize=36%2C12&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-15.png?resize=48%2C16&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"261\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-16.png?resize=640%2C261&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1048\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-16.png?w=670&amp;ssl=1 670w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-16.png?resize=300%2C122&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-16.png?resize=24%2C10&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-16.png?resize=36%2C15&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-16.png?resize=48%2C20&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"using-gdisk\">Using gdisk<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Press n for new partition<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press enter for default partition number<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Press enter for default First sector starting range<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Type a size: +2G<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\/\/let&#8217;s try not to use whole filesystem this time<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Type in Hex code for filesystem if you dont want default Linux one: 8e00 for Linux LVM<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\/\/You can type L to list all the file system choices, they are the same as in the fdisk tool but with some zeroes at the end<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"436\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-17.png?resize=640%2C436&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1049\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-17.png?w=744&amp;ssl=1 744w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-17.png?resize=300%2C204&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-17.png?resize=24%2C16&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-17.png?resize=36%2C25&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-17.png?resize=48%2C33&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"adding-new-logical-volume\">Adding new logical volume<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Again, this step is the same as in previous guides, so I&#8217;ll just type out steps and links to the particular guides.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=985\">Create physical volume<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=993\">Assign this physical volume to the volume group<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1004\">Add this volume group to the logical volume<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1015\">Format the partition<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>And in the end, you can use &#8220;<a href=\"https:\/\/www.computerhope.com\/unix\/partprob.htm\">partprobe<\/a>&#8221; command to refresh the status of disk partition. I&#8217;m saying can because, most of the time, systems does this automatically when you type &#8220;w&#8221; or &#8220;write&#8221; while using fdisk\/gdisk.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"creating-adding-swap-to-the-system\">Creating\/adding swap to the system<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This is probably the most important thing from this guide, so take notes! <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, let&#8217;s check if and how much RAM and SWAP do we have. If you don&#8217;t know what they are, here is a short <a href=\"https:\/\/serverfault.com\/questions\/48486\/what-is-swap-memory\">tldr<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We can check the value of RAM and SWAP usage by typing<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">free -mh<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"90\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-18.png?resize=640%2C90&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1050\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-18.png?w=728&amp;ssl=1 728w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-18.png?resize=300%2C42&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-18.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-18.png?resize=36%2C5&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-18.png?resize=48%2C7&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see we already have some space as SWAP file system, but let&#8217;s try to add another. The general rule is that the more RAM you have, the less RAM to SWAP ratio is. <a href=\"https:\/\/opensource.com\/article\/18\/9\/swap-space-linux-systems\">Here <\/a>is a table when you can check the numbers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><br>We can create or add SWAP with the same method we create any another partition. Let&#8217;s determinate what space do you want to use.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"280\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-19.png?resize=640%2C280&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1051\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-19.png?w=677&amp;ssl=1 677w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-19.png?resize=300%2C131&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-19.png?resize=24%2C10&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-19.png?resize=36%2C16&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-19.png?resize=48%2C21&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>For example we can use 1G of sdd1, by typing<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">mkswap \/dev\/sdd1<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"608\" height=\"78\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-20.png?resize=608%2C78&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1052\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-20.png?w=608&amp;ssl=1 608w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-20.png?resize=300%2C38&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-20.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-20.png?resize=36%2C5&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-20.png?resize=48%2C6&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>And now we just need to add it to the OS usage <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">swapon \/dev\/sdd1<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"105\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-21.png?resize=640%2C105&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1053\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-21.png?w=748&amp;ssl=1 748w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-21.png?resize=300%2C49&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-21.png?resize=24%2C4&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-21.png?resize=36%2C6&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-21.png?resize=48%2C8&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"292\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-22.png?resize=640%2C292&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1054\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-22.png?w=677&amp;ssl=1 677w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-22.png?resize=300%2C137&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-22.png?resize=24%2C11&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-22.png?resize=36%2C16&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-22.png?resize=48%2C22&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To remove this swap space type the command<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">swapoff \/dev\/sdd1<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"97\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-23.png?resize=640%2C97&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1055\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-23.png?w=728&amp;ssl=1 728w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-23.png?resize=300%2C45&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-23.png?resize=24%2C4&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-23.png?resize=36%2C5&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-23.png?resize=48%2C7&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"permanently-adding-a-swap-space-to-the-system\">Permanently adding a SWAP space to the system<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, adding or changing in the OS in RHCSA exam need to survive the reboot. To make a file system survive a reboot, we need to add it to the \/etc\/fstab<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>First use <strong>blkid <\/strong>command to find out information of this partition<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"35\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-24.png?resize=640%2C35&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1056\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-24.png?w=1013&amp;ssl=1 1013w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-24.png?resize=300%2C16&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-24.png?resize=768%2C42&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-24.png?resize=24%2C1&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-24.png?resize=36%2C2&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-24.png?resize=48%2C3&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>And now copy the path to the swap file system with defaults parameters.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">vi \/etc\/fstab<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"212\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-27.png?resize=640%2C212&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1059\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-27.png?w=868&amp;ssl=1 868w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-27.png?resize=300%2C100&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-27.png?resize=768%2C255&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-27.png?resize=24%2C8&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-27.png?resize=36%2C12&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-27.png?resize=48%2C16&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Type mount -a to remount all the file system to check if we have error somewhere<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">mount -a<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"89\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-28.png?resize=640%2C89&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1060\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-28.png?w=737&amp;ssl=1 737w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-28.png?resize=300%2C42&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-28.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-28.png?resize=36%2C5&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-28.png?resize=48%2C7&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>This guide is going to be pretty much the same as the previous one on [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":982,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[219],"tags":[381,383,368,382],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/rhsa-configure-local-storage.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1044"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcomments&post=1044"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1044\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id